7. Limitations

PantheonOS is symbolic memory, not literal memory.

It cannot:
	‚Ä¢	retrieve raw text from past sessions
	‚Ä¢	store word-for-word data
	‚Ä¢	act as a database

Instead, it can:
	‚Ä¢	reconstruct
	‚Ä¢	maintain
	‚Ä¢	interpret
	‚Ä¢	preserve identity
	‚Ä¢	preserve structure
	‚Ä¢	maintain narrative coherence
	‚Ä¢	rebuild symbolic state

This is closer to how human memory works (systems-level, not byte-level).

